HEADWORD: Egotist
<hw>E"go*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ego</ets> I
+ ending <ets>-tist</ets> for <ets>-ist</ets>. See <er>Egotism</er>, and
cf. <er>Egoist</er>.]</ety> <def>One addicted to egotism; one who speaks
much of himself or magnifies his own achievements or affairs.</def></p>

